==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bleeding
<hw>Bleed"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Emitting, or appearing to emit,
blood or sap, etc.; also, expressing anguish or compassion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bleeding</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bleeding
<hw>Bleed"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A running or issuing of blood, as
from the nose or a wound; a hemorrhage; the operation of letting blood,
as in surgery; a drawing or running of sap from a tree or
plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bleep</ent>⟦br⟧
